20 minutes ago, OliviaaF said:

The exact one.

The message.

Interesting, I definitely don't get that.  Maybe try removing the mod entirely and re-installing it from a fresh download.  It could be that there's an old file in there that didn't get overwritten, and that's what it's seeing.  If that doesn't work, I might be able to see what's going on by looking at KSP's log.  Instructions on how to find and upload that are in the first link in my signature.

Edited April 24, 2017 by blowfish

1 hour ago, blowfish said:

Interesting, I definitely don't get that.  Maybe try removing the mod entirely and re-installing it.  It could be that there's an old file in there that didn't get overwritten, and that's what it's seeing.

Deleted and tried again. Same thing. I'm gonna reinstall KSP, to make sure it's up to date

I don't think there's a built in KSP version check in any version of this plugin (I rely on KSP AVC for that sort of stuff, and I dont recall that in the original either). You sure that's not from one of the core B9 procedural plugins?

I don't think there's a built in KSP version check in any version of this plugin (I rely on KSP AVC for that sort of stuff, and I dont recall that in the original either). You sure that's not from one of the core B9 procedural plugins?

It honestly could be. I'm reinstalling to be safe. 

 

Edit: Got rid of B9, and installed it fresh, which works.

Edited April 24, 2017 by OliviaaF

Just a really quick question that might make it easier for people (like me) trying to recreate real vehicles based on their specified size:

Is there a consistent unit of length used throughout the wing manipulation interfaces? If so, how does this unit relate to the in-game meter? What about wing thicknesses?

 

Thanks a lot!
B9 PWings uses whatever the game has decided is 1m along all axes

as of now, if I am not mistaken, you support fuel in your wings only if we have modular fuel tanks installed.  My question is could you also check for Configurable Containers and add the fuel in the wings if we have this one instead?
Fuel support also works for stock, but it does appear another special case would be beneficial for Configurable Containers

Don't know if anyone else has flagged this, but I get a launch error (in KSP 1.3) at the same place every time:

Edited May 27, 2017 by TMS

There seems to be some kind of strange behavior when using the "Deploy" option on control surfaces. See the picture below.

B9-PCSA control surfaces (on the lower portion of the spaceplane) are working as intended and both are deploying in the same direction. B9-PCST surfaces (upper portion of the spaceplane) on the other hand are deploying in different directions. I'm using radial symmetry in both cases. Is this a bug or some kind of intended behaviour I couldn't figure out?
Does anyone know if this works in 1.3 yet?

24 minutes ago, Brainpop14 said:

Does anyone know if this works in 1.3 yet?

Yes

Hey guys for some reason my B9 UI is not showing up when i press J...any advice on what i can do to make it reappear?

Also when i try to launch any of my craft all the PWings are out of shape and my craft explodes on runway.  


Im on 1.3

Update  ok after sifting through the other mods i figured out the problem is the B9 aerospace/legacy/HX parts mod.  I did install it correctly with all the up to date associated mods that need to go with it, but the problem is still there.... Let me know if anyone else is having this problem? 

Edited June 22, 2017 by mechanicH

On 2017/6/21 at 4:38 PM, mechanicH said:

Hey guys for some reason my B9 UI is not showing up when i press J...any advice on what i can do to make it reappear?

Also when i try to launch any of my craft all the PWings are out of shape and my craft explodes on runway.  


Im on 1.3

Update  ok after sifting through the other mods i figured out the problem is the B9 aerospace/legacy/HX parts mod.  I did install it correctly with all the up to date associated mods that need to go with it, but the problem is still there.... Let me know if anyone else is having this problem? 

I have the same problem. After a long test I find that the reason is the Module Manager 2.8.1 conflict with this Procedural Wing. I changed my Module Manager back to 2.7.6 and then it works when I press J.

However, Module Manager 2.8.1 is required by B9 Part Switch in ksp1.3, so I cannot use this mod with B9 main part at the same time. I think there's still some problem with Module Manager 2.8.1.

2 hours ago, msssaf said:

Module Manager 2.8.1 is required by B9 Part Switch in ksp1.3, so I cannot use this mod with B9 main part at the same time. I think there's still some problem with Module Manager 2.8.1.

Good catch. Never crossed my mind to look at the MM. I kept thinking I messed up on properly updating the requirements. Might have to get @sarbian input on this one.

15 hours ago, msssaf said:

I think there's still some problem with Module Manager 2.8.1.

And I think not. Since 1.3 got out each time someone said that it turned out they had a mod compiled for 1.2 installed.

6 hours ago, sarbian said:

And I think not. Since 1.3 got out each time someone said that it turned out they had a mod compiled for 1.2 installed.

So do you mean that some mods like this p-wing which said that they support ksp 1.3 are not actually support 1.3? I mean this is not the only one which I found that conflict with MM 2.8.1...

All this stuff is still being ironed out for 1.3. I'm sure it will get resolved. As for now I had to take out the B9 aerospace parts pack HX and legacy for the B9 PWings to work properly. I already mentioned this to blowfish. Hopefully when he has time he will take a look at it too

On 7/8/2017 at 8:48 AM, sarbian said:

And I think not. Since 1.3 got out each time someone said that it turned out they had a mod compiled for 1.2 installed.

As some one that downloaded the B9 pwings mod from the link from Blowfish, 4 post above your's, I can confirm that v0.40.13 of b9 pwings does not work when 2.8.1 of MM is present
 
This is was tested on a clean install with just  b9 pwings and MM 

Edit:
WTK, I re-tried it and it seemes to have worked after properly with the above versions of each mod

 

Edited July 12, 2017 by Grease1991

Ok So after some trial an error i've found two thing that somehow cause the issue, 
I have installed 
B9 PWings (duh)
B9 Aerospace, (with updated RPM, animation Modules, and B9 Part Switcher Smokescreen and Firespitter)
B9 HX
B9 Legacy 
and
AoATech, (comes bundled with a folder called ASET)
and MM 2.8.1
now heres the weird part. I can either delete the B9 legacy folder OR delete AoATech with its ASET bundle and get Pwings to work, 
I tried it with an install with the mentioned above and my kraken calling install and it works with both. 

Apologies to Sarbian for potentially wasting his time by looking at MM, as going from 1.8.1 back to 1.8.0 did nothing, and going from 1.8.x to 1.7.6 created a different issue that prevented me from testing the current one. 

I hope this helps someone with more codeknowhow to figure out what the technical reason is for this glitch.
Would really like to see logs from someone who is seeing this issue.  Everyone seems to be blaming a different mod that doesn't even interact with PWings.

Oh, I bet this is it 

[LOG 10:20:33.621] Config(@PART[AoAero.TESTFin]:FOR[FerramAerospaceResearch]) AoATech/Parts/Aero/TestFin/TESTFin/@PART[AoAero.TESTFin]:FOR[FerramAerospaceResearch]

A patch marked FOR[FerramAerospaceResearch] tells KSP that FerramAerospaceResearch and so any patch marked NEEDS[FerramAerospaceResearch] will be processed.  You should tell the author of AoA Tech about that.
Is there any quick way to fix that and see if it solves the issue?

2 minutes ago, Grease1991 said:

Is there any quick way to fix that and see if it solves the issue?

Yeah, in AoATech/Parts/Aero/TestFin/TESTFin.cfg, you should see a node: 

@PART[AoAero.TESTFin]:FOR[FerramAerospaceResearch] { ... }

Change it to 

@PART[AoAero.TESTFin]:NEEDS[FerramAerospaceResearch] { ... }
